HERE IS A SIMPLE TRICK TO CONVERT THIS PROBLEM INTO HOUSE-ROBBER;

Given:  unsorted array of positive integers;
 problem: Pick any array[i] and delete it to earn array[i] points. Afterwards, you must delete every element equal to array[i] - 1 and every element equal to array[i] + 1;

solution :
step 1 : sort the array(this will help us to bring all repeated value together and also help us to align array[i] with array[i]-1 and array[i]+1 {if array[i]+1 or array[i]-1 are there })

step 2 : create a empty integer vector name houses and a int sum=array[0] ;

step 3: run a loop from 0 to n-2 , where n is array size  and inside this loop 


          if (array[i]==array[i+1] ) {
          sum+=array[i];}
// (here we calculate the total of array [i] i.e array[i] * x, where x is no. of times value at array[i] is repeted )

                                    else
                                    {
                                       houses.push_back(sum);    
                                       sum=array[i+1];  // replace the sum with current integer;
                                  // ( we enter the total value for our array[i-1] intger )
step 4:  we check if next int value is +1 of previous value or not;

                           if(array[i]!=array[i+1]-1) {
                            houses.push_back(0) 
                           }
                            }// close braces for else
(if  next different value is not a +1 value then that means we don't have to delete any one of these values to get our max answer at that point.
 therefore we enter a house with 0 value in middle of these two values 
  houses )

END; (above array is now converted to houses on which you can apply house-robber solution)

